!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

clause /klɔːz/

(clauses) 

1. N-COUNT A clause is a section of a legal document. (法律文件的) 条款 

例： He has a clause in his contract which entitles him to a percentage of the profits. 他在他的合同里有一项条款保证他享有一定比例的利润。 

例： ...a compromise document sprinkled with escape clauses. …一份满是免责条款的妥协性文件。 

2. N-COUNT In grammar, a clause is a group of words containing a verb. Sentences contain one or more clauses. 分句

</div>

